# Netlify _headers — Gläserne Leidenschaft
# Purpose: make sure the app shell (index.html) is ALWAYS revalidated, so a
# visitor can never be served a stale, out-of-date copy of the site. This is
# what prevents the "old cached page shows old data" problem (e.g. a product
# name a customer sees that no longer matches the live database).
#
# How it works: "max-age=0, must-revalidate" lets the browser keep a copy but
# forces it to check with the server on every load. Netlify uses ETags, so if
# nothing changed the server replies "304 Not Modified" (fast, no re-download);
# if you've deployed an update, the visitor gets the new version immediately.
#
# Placement: this file must be named exactly  _headers  (no extension) and sit
# in the SAME folder as index.html in your Netlify deploy.

/
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

/index.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
